Computer architects sometimes find it useful to characterize cache misses
by type. There are 3 types of cache misses:
- Compulsory (or cold-start) miss:
  The cache is empty and this is the first reference to the item.
- Capacity miss:
  The cache run out of space and had to take out an item from the cache
  to bring a new item into the cache.
- Conflict miss:
  The miss happen because the item can not be placed in the cache by some
  limitation known as "set-associativity" (?).

